      "title": "Solve for y",
      "content": "Isolate $y$ in the equation:<br/>$$\\frac{3}{5}x+\\frac{3}{4}y=8$$<br/>$$\\frac{3}{4}y=8-\\frac{3}{5}x$$<br/>$$y=\\frac{4}{3}\\left(8-\\frac{3}{5}x\\right)=\\frac{32}{3}-\\frac{4}{5}x$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Evaluate the listed x-values",
      "content": "For $x=1$, $y=\\frac{32}{3}-\\frac{4}{5}=\\frac{160}{15}-\\frac{12}{15}=\\frac{148}{15}$. For $x=2$, $y=\\frac{32}{3}-\\frac{8}{5}=\\frac{160}{15}-\\frac{24}{15}=\\frac{136}{15}$. For $x=4$, $y=\\frac{32}{3}-\\frac{16}{5}=\\frac{160}{15}-\\frac{48}{15}=\\frac{112}{15}$."
